# Playwright artifact gitignore.
#
# Visual regression baselines (PNG screenshots) are NOT committed because
# Windows / Linux CI / macOS pixel rendering drift makes binary baselines
# fragile across environments. Each developer / CI environment regenerates
# its own baseline on first run via:
#
#     npm run test:visual:update -w @sikao/web
#
# The spec files + playwright.config.ts ARE tracked so the test
# infrastructure reproduces; baseline PNGs are local artifacts.
#
# Snapshot directories playwright produces:
#   <spec-name>.spec.ts-snapshots/   (default naming)
#   __snapshots__/                    (alternative if snapshotDir is set)

# All snapshot directories
**/*-snapshots/
**/__snapshots__/

# Catch-all for stray PNG / WebM trace artifacts in this tree
*.png
*.webm
*.zip

# Playwright run results / HTML report (also rooted at apps/web/)
# These already live outside e2e/, see apps/web/.gitignore for those.
